# Auto-push to GitHub

When the user asks you to update, fix, add, or change anything in the code for this project:

1. Make the code changes.
2. Commit with a concise message focused on why.
3. Push to `origin` on the current branch (default: `main` → `https://github.com/beta-works1/simulations`).

Do this without waiting for a separate "push" or "commit" request, unless the user explicitly says not to push.

Still follow normal git safety: no force-push, no amending others' commits, no committing secrets.
